BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:WiQceIkBPXptbmtJeN0Kw
SUMMARY:Alela Diane\, guests
DTSTAMP:20260314T153646Z
DTSTART:20260619T030000Z
DESCRIPTION:Advance: $20 ($26.27 after fees)\n\nDay of: $25 ($31.42 after f
	ees)\n\nAlela Diane:\n\nMore than a decade into one of contemporary folk’s
	 most quietly extraordinary careers\, Alela Diane returns on May 22 with W
	ho's Keeping Time? via Fluff & Gravy / Loose Music.\n\nThe Portland songwr
	iter’s seventh full-length album came as the consequence of intuition\, co
	incidence\, and community. On the first of April last year\, Michael Hurle
	y\, folk legend and indispensable presence in the Portland music scene\, d
	ied at the age of eighty-three. “I was absolutely gutted\,” says Alela\, w
	ho didn’t just revere Hurley but knew him well. She performed in a tribute
	 show for Hurley\, and in that collective mourning\, found solace and insp
	iration. “It was an epiphany to realize how much I missed my community. I 
	felt very clear about what I wanted in that moment—I want to be alive. I w
	ant to see live music. I want to play it.”\n\nThough she’d taken the solo 
	route on her last handful of releases\, Alela was interested in a new way 
	forward. Plucking the day away in the attic of her 1892 Victorian home\, s
	he found new songs flickering in the dusty light—and a desire to play them
	 with people.\n\nAlela met drummer Danny Austin-Manning at Clay Street Stu
	dios one night and he introduced her to co-producer Sam Weber (Madison Cun
	ningham\, Anna Tivel). Along with Sebastian Owens on bass\, they recorded 
	fifteen songs in less than five days—all live in the very attic where she 
	wrote them. Anna Tivel contributed backing vocals and violin. Peter Lalish
	\, of the band Lucius\, added guitar. Fellow Pacific Northwesterners Kati 
	Claborn and Luke Ydstie of Blind Pilot and AC Sapphire provided overdubs o
	f all kinds. Alela’s vision for uninhibited music and revived\, creative k
	inship thrust her into a new season.\n\nThe result is an 11-track set rang
	ing from lulling to raw to cinematic\, with Alela’s mellifluous voice a li
	vely and affecting instrument throughout. The lyrics reveal an artist with
	 the particular kind of strength required to face pain without getting los
	t—an ability Alela has honed over a lifetime of songwriting\, during which
	 her lustrous discography has garnered major critical acclaim from the lik
	es of Pitchfork\, NPR Music\, The Guardian\, and plenty more. UNCUT has ch
	aracterized her skill as “insanely beautiful\, with the strength and delic
	acy of spider silk” while counting her work among the ‘50 best singer-song
	writer albums’ of all time—a canon comprising John Lennon\, Joni Mitchell\
	, Joan Baez\, and Paul Simon. Consequence has echoed that significance\, d
	eclaring\, “Hers is a timeless sound\, that of a wayfaring troubadour\, wh
	ich only seems to come a few times a generation.”\n\nWith Who’s Keeping Ti
	me?\, Alela Diane transforms grief into gathering\, reaffirming her place 
	as a vital\, living force in contemporary folk music—rooted in community\,
	 presence\, and the enduring power of song.\n\nPlease note\, the Sunset Ta
	vern is a strictly 21+ bar and venue and does not accept vertical ID’s for
	 entry.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/V58bff8a810e\n\nFrom Sunset Tavern
URL:https://link.dice.fm/V58bff8a810e
LOCATION:5433 Ballard Avenue Northwest\, Seattle\, Washington 98107\, Unite
	d States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:sunset-tavern
CATEGORIES:Sunset Tavern
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
